2.title: Voiceover Artists and the Utah Film Commision
2.plot: On this episode I am chatting with Brenda Upright and Brenda Robinson about their workshops that are coming to Utah for voice-over Artist. I will also be chatting with Utah's Film Commissioner Marshall More about what the film commission is doing to drive more films to the state.

3.title: Cannoli, CS6, Fact or Faked: Paranormal Files, and the Mine
3.plot: On this episode I am chatting with Rachel McCash, Mike Schreurs, chatting about their new film Cannoli and Pamela Ann Berry is here to talk about what to expect in CS6. I also chat with cast members at The Mine Premier as well as Ben Hansen from SyFy's hit TV show "Fact or Faked: Paranormal Files"

4.title: Last Man on Earth, Making History Hot, Heartbeat
4.plot: Talking to Charan Prabhakar from "The Mine" and "Last Man's on Earth", Kira Peacock from "Making History Hot" and Jeff Yeats from many films and music videos including "Heartbeat" from the New Electric Sound.

5.title: Friend Request, Virgin Diaries, Utah Film Commision Helping Local Films
5.plot: On this episode of Filmed in Utah I'm chatting with Jarrod Phillips from Friend Request, Skippy Jessop from TLC's Virgin Diaries, and Marshall More about how the film commission is here to help local filmmakers.

7.title: Zombie Hunters, Modeling in Utah, Viral Videos
7.plot: On this episode, Danny Trejo says which one of his characters could destroy Chuck Norris, Kyle Demontmorency talks about how taking acting classes helps his modeling career, and Ryan + Paul Richardson chat about their work with Teddy Films Star Wars parody's and the Doritos Superbowl commercial winner.

8.title: Amy Lia, Keith, Keith Hottinger, Clark Edmunds and Orc Wars
8.plot: On this episode I am talking to 2 actors on how they prepare for TV and film roles, and I am also chatting with a professional practical FX artist. I also speak with the director and lead actor on the set of the new fantasy action film "Orc Wars".

9.title: Too Many Legs Animation Studio, Thor Media, Dave Hunter of 'Nitro Circus'
9.plot: On this episode I am talking to Too Many Legs Animation Studio about what it takes for an aspiring animation artist to get into this business, Thor Media about their app development and post production expertise, and Dave Hunter who has produced films such as The Singles Ward, Mobsters and Mormons, and most recently Nitro Circus 3D for MTV and Heavens Door for Hallmark!

10.title: Day Zero and Think Outside the Blog
10.plot: The cast of the award winning webs series "Day Zero" talk about their experiences on the show and new projects the cast is currently involved in.

11.title: The Inner B and Tattle Tail
11.plot: On this weeks episode of Filmed in Utah I am chatting with Jamielee Eldridge about her recent short films, Cathleen Mason about what it takes to be an actress in Utah, and Dusti Jones about her experiences as a producer, singer and actress. And Evie Atchison is on location chatting with filmmakers at the Salty Horror International Film Festival. It's all coming up on Filmed in Utah!

12.title: Remind, Father of the Year, Four Weeks
12.plot: This weeks episode is all about student made projects including Remind, Father of the Year, and Four Weeks.
